The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Spencers pares losses 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Spencers pares losses 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, June 21: Spencers  the retail arm of city-based RPG Enterprises  has improved its operating performance in the last fiscal.        
	The company, which sells food, apparel and consumer durables through multiple retail formats, has reported a dip in both sales and losses in 2009-10. However, the loss reduction has outstripped the slide in sales, indicating a better show.        
	A wholly owned subsidiary of CESC, Spencers has reported a 9.8 per cent fall in revenue at Rs 965 crore against Rs 1,071 crore a year ago.         
	However, the company has been able to pare its losses by 21.1 per cent to Rs 351 crore compared with Rs 445 crore a year ago, CESCs consolidated results showed.        
	The company had said it intended to break even by the end of this fiscal. Last year, it had closed down some small stores to focus on the bigger outlets.        
	CESC profit        
	CESC has posted a consolidated profit after tax of Rs 157 crore during 2009-10 against Rs 77 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
